subject: Swimming
lead_paragraph: FINA, swimming’s governing body, rejected 10 high-tech racing suits and approved 202 others Tuesday for the world championships in July. FINA said its panel sent 136 models back to the manufacturers, who have 30 days to submit modified designs.
